Avon Call-Options Volume Rises to Highest Level in Three Months

-- B y   J e f f   K e a r n s
-- 
2011-08-12T18:49:25Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/avon-call-options-volume-rises-to-highest-level-in-three-months.html
Avon Products Inc. (AVP) ’s bullish options
trading jumped to a three-month high on speculation that the
world’s largest door-to-door cosmetics merchant will reverse its
three-week decline.  More than 15,000 calls to buy the stock changed hands as of
2:42 p.m. in  New York , seven times the four-week average and 40
times the number of puts to sell. Two-thirds of all volume was
concentrated in the January $22.50 calls, which rose 11 percent.
The shares, which gained 1.1 percent to $21.23 today, are down
27 percent from a seven-week high of $28.90 on July 21.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jeff Kearns in New York at 
